\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Virtual Chamber Thermodynamics. (a) Temperature (teal, left axis) and pressure (coral, right axis, kPa) as functions of molecule count during chamber population from hardware oscillations; temperature stabilises near $0.083$ while pressure decreases from $73.8$~kPa to $29.2$~kPa as the ensemble equilibrates. (b) Histogram of the $S_e$ distribution across 1{,}000 molecules in 10 bins; the near-uniform distribution (dashed line = mean count) confirms that the energy coordinate explores its full range, with variance $= 0.0829$. (c) Three-dimensional scatter of 100 timing samples in (sample time~$\mu $s, $S_t$, $S_e$) space, coloured by $S_e$; the clustering of $S_t$ near unity reflects sub-microsecond timing precision. (d) S-coordinate profiles $(S_k, S_t, S_e)$ for five categorical navigation targets spanning room temperature to the solar centre; all locations are accessed instantaneously with no spatial propagation, demonstrating that categorical address resolution is independent of physical scale.}}{11}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:arch_panel3_thermodynamics}{{2}{11}{Virtual Chamber Thermodynamics. (a) Temperature (teal, left axis) and pressure (coral, right axis, kPa) as functions of molecule count during chamber population from hardware oscillations; temperature stabilises near $0.083$ while pressure decreases from $73.8$~kPa to $29.2$~kPa as the ensemble equilibrates. (b) Histogram of the $S_e$ distribution across 1{,}000 molecules in 10 bins; the near-uniform distribution (dashed line = mean count) confirms that the energy coordinate explores its full range, with variance $= 0.0829$. (c) Three-dimensional scatter of 100 timing samples in (sample time~$\mu $s, $S_t$, $S_e$) space, coloured by $S_e$; the clustering of $S_t$ near unity reflects sub-microsecond timing precision. (d) S-coordinate profiles $(S_k, S_t, S_e)$ for five categorical navigation targets spanning room temperature to the solar centre; all locations are accessed instantaneously with no spatial propagation, demonstrating that categorical address resolution is independent of physical scale}{figure.2}{}}
